The input `maxTime` is a positive integer.
The input `edges` is a 2D integer array where each element `edges[i]` is an array of length - The input `passingFees` is a 0-indexed integer array of length `n`.
The length of `passingFees` is equal to `n`, where `n` is the number of cities.
The input `edges` represents the roads between cities, where each road is represented as an array `[x, y, time]`.
The input `edges` does not contain any road that connects a city to itself.
The input `edges` may contain multiple roads of differing travel times connecting the same two cities.
The input `maxTime` represents the maximum time in minutes to reach city `n - 1`.
The input `passingFees[j]` represents the amount of dollars to pay when passing through city `j`.
The source city is city `0` and the destination city is city `n - 1`.
